**Sliding Window O(n + m):** Need-freq map of t. Window-freq + matched counter (kitne distinct chars ki freq exact match hai). Right expand, jab matched == required (distinct in t), left se contract aur best length update.

Leftmost preserve karne ke liye sirf STRICTLY smaller length pe update — equal length pe ignore (kyunki leftmost wala pehle aaya).

```js
function smallestContainingSubstr(s, t) {
  if (t.length > s.length) return "";
  const need = {};
  for (const c of t) need[c] = (need[c] || 0) + 1;
  const required = Object.keys(need).length;
  const window = {};
  let have = 0, l = 0;
  let bestL = -1, bestLen = Infinity;
  for (let r = 0; r < s.length; r++) {
    const c = s[r];
    window[c] = (window[c] || 0) + 1;
    if (need[c] !== undefined && window[c] === need[c]) have++;
    while (have === required) {
      if (r - l + 1 < bestLen) { bestLen = r - l + 1; bestL = l; }
      const lc = s[l];
      window[lc]--;
      if (need[lc] !== undefined && window[lc] < need[lc]) have--;
      l++;
    }
  }
  return bestL === -1 ? "" : s.substring(bestL, bestL + bestLen);
}
```

**Time:** O(n). **Space:** O(unique chars in t).

